			<title><![CDATA[ Gallery Reveals Secret Gizmodo Production Chain ]]></title>
			<description><![CDATA[ <p><img src="http://cache.gawker.com/assets/images/gizmodo/2008/12/gizslaves.jpg" width="804" height="535" style="display:block;float:none;" />Those who came to the gallery were able to get a glimpse of this: The usual suspects doing their thing. Did you ever wonder how all the Giz's magic and nonsense happens? Here's is how it <i>basically</i> works:</p> <p><script type="text/javascript" charset="utf-8"> galleryPost('gizslaves', 3, ''); </script></p> <p>10 news pop<br> 20 Adam checks <a href="http://gizmodo.com/gadgets/oh,-food!-i.ll-just-_-wahhhhhh!!/squirrel-catapult-is-awful-yet-we-cant-look-away-270290.php">flying_squirrels=</a>A$<br> 30 if A$=yes then gosub 120<br> 40 John checks <a href="http://gizmodo.com/5075490/nasas-phoenix-mars-lander-guest-blogging-on-giz">martians</a>=B$<br> 50 if B$=yes then gosub 140<br> 60 Jesus checks <a href="http://gizmodo.com/5018990/lego-secret-vault-contains-all-sets-in-history">lego_bricks</a>=C$<br> 70 if C$=yes then gosub 160<br> 80 Matt checks <a href="http://gizmodo.com/5103031/motorola-is-officially-junk">motorola_death</a>=D$<br> 90 if D$=yes then gosub 190<br> 100 brian prints "It's the Internet, FIND MORE THINGS! DO FEATURES! WRITE! WORK! JUMP!"<br> 110 goto 10<br> 120 Adam writes furry remarks<br> 130 end<br> 140 John writes scientific blurb<br> 150 end<br> 160 Jesus writes about cocktails<br> 170 Jesus stomps around in <a href="http://gizmodo.com/5063902/japanese-gundam-slippers-make-giant-robot-noises">Gundam slippers</a><br> 180 end<br> 190 Matt rejoices<br> 200 end</p> <p>And that's basically the New York-based Gizmodo <s>slavery</s> blogging program works, thank you very much.</p> <p><i>[I know my basic is bad, <a href="http://gizmodo.com/gadgets/piece-of-cake/how-to-install-apps-on-your-iphone-easily-no-hacking-skills-required-291184.php">TFSU</a>]</i></p> ]]></description>
